<br>
Sometime in 1986 (or there-abouts), while going to a Navy school, I was Game Master for a group of AD&amp;D players. We played what was probably the best session I had ever Game Mastered using the Ravenloft Module.  Because my mind was on undead, vampires and the lot, when I picked up a Dragon Magazine that had a ruleset for a Witch type of character, I decided to see what I could come up with for a good NPC to play against my players.<br>
<br>
Thus was born the Witch, Sapphire L'ree. Sapphire being an indication of her power level which I found appropriate to my campaign. I frankly don't remember if the name Loreana Shahnra was thought of before or after, but I suspect before.<br>
<br>
I didn't have a chance to use her in the campaign though. But I *was* very interested in my creation. Something so beautiful and so evil was fascinating to me.  I wrote my first short-short about her sometime in 1987/88: the demon summoning, which is in Chapter 9 as a flashback.<br>
<br>
I had written a few shorts about her and thought about how to use her in a campaign once I started playing again, but she didn't develop much beyond that for a few years.<br>
<br>
Around 1990, I wrote a short-short: The Beginning (now Chapter 50). It has been heavily modified because it was not originally part of any story, just some background information on the source of L'ree's evil. Her father's part in it was added several years later.<br>
<br>
Around the same time I wrote the 'The Bear Tamer' short-short (now in Chapter 6). An origin for Sapphire L'ree's path of darkness she would take in her life.<br>
<br>
In 1992, I chose to use L'ree in a game GM'd by a friend. Because she had no use in the game as a totally evil character, I softened her a bit. Defined her evil, if you will. Instead of evil for evil's sake, I filled out her tortured past. Her search for power, convinced it could right the wrongs, drove her to the darker side of power.<br>
<br>
Suddenly the creation that had originally fascinated me, now had captured me. In 1994, I began to wrack my brain. How can I change this totally evil creature to a hero? I wanted to write about her, wanted it desperately for reasons few people know, reasons I myself didn't know until about a year ago *hugs Ninou tightly*.  But I didn't want to change Sapphire L'ree.<br>
<br>
That was when the dual nature of Loreana/L'ree was born. I gave my evil Sapphire L'ree her 'Second Chance'. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Once I topped that peak, the writing flowed. The story wrote itself, things I never intended, never thought of writing, got written. Pippen, Denan and Megda just happened, Cruzaz Ror, Sandrak Desmane and Guptras Den's stories are just starting (and still needing to be filled out in what I have already written, though the story stands fine as-is).  I wrote in a frenzy from 1994 to 1998.  A frenzy because the story often came to me in bits and pieces, chapters coming out of sequence and horribly written in pencil on a steno pad while I was out to sea on another submarine.  Not only was the story written, but the world of Andar more fully fleshed out, the races and rules of magic defined (and separated from their AD&amp;D origins), the gods created, the history and politics written.  The Dwarven language is still being created, an extremely difficult process for somebody who only knows one language and isn't particularly interested in the rules behind that one. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  (gods I hated High School English). I even designed the written, Dwarven, base 12 number system (don't ask why, it will most likely never be used).<br>
<br>
All of that to write this story that wanted to be written.<br>
<br>
Aside from bits and pieces in the future of the story, the writing frenzy stopped sometime around 1998/99. The two Lora's finally discovered their beginnings, their connection. There's more to be written, but the part that really needed to come out, did.<br>
There's a whole lot more to their story however...I just need to write it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Oh yea, and sometime in late 1999 I discovered Evercrack, created Dorraxx from a previous AD&amp;D character nowhere near as old as L'ree, then created the Necromancer Loreana Shahnra.  You will see Dorraxx sometime in the near future in The Second Chance. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center>
